  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (MRL 3, W-EP-04)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 3. Twelve of thirteen credibility factors are assessed and meet required levels. One factor — Equivalency of input parameters — is recorded as not-assessed on the grounds that it 'does not apply to a purely computational sensitivity study'; however, the correct encoding for a non-applicable factor would be factorStatus not-applicable, and the absence of a formal assessment at MRL 3 materially weakens credibility.",
